<item>
            <title>[SPARK-11276] SizeEstimator prevents class unloading</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-11276</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The SizeEstimator keeps a cache of ClassInfos but this cache uses Class objects as keys.&lt;br/&gt;
Which results in strong references to the Class objects. If these classes are dynamically created&lt;br/&gt;
this prevents the corresponding ClassLoader from being GCed. Leading to PermGen exhaustion.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;An easy fix would be to use a WeakRef for the keys. A proposed fix can be found here:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/Site2Mobile/spark/commit/21c572cbda5607d0c7c6643bfaf43e53c8aa6f8c&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/Site2Mobile/spark/commit/21c572cbda5607d0c7c6643bfaf43e53c8aa6f8c&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
We are currently running this in production and it seems to resolve the issue.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I will prepare a pull request ASAP.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
